Setup:

#import libraries
library(ggplot2)
library(plyr)
library(grid)
setwd("~/Documents/Data_Visualization/data-viz/ebola")
germs <- read.csv("Microbe-scope-bugs.csv")

Ensure that data entries for fatality rate and contagiousness are of numeric class. Combine the airborne and airborne droplet entries to have one airborne category.

#eliminate non-numeric entries
germsnumeric <- germs[3:41,]

#function to remove percents from entries
dropPct<-function(df, var){
  dropPct<-strsplit(as.character(df[[var]]), split="%")
  df[[var]]<-as.numeric(dropPct)
  return(df[[var]])
  }

#remove percents from fatality rates
germsnumeric[["case.fatality.rate"]]<-dropPct(germsnumeric, "case.fatality.rate")

#convert factor entries for fatality and contagiousness to numeric
germinfect <- germsnumeric$average.basic.reproductive.rate
germinfect <- as.numeric(levels(germinfect))[germinfect]
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
germsnumeric$average.basic.reproductive.rate <- germinfect

#replace 'airborne droplet' with 'airborne' to create one airborne category
germsnumeric$primary.mode.of.transmission <- revalue(germsnumeric$primary.mode.of.transmission, c("airborne droplet" = "airborne"))

#remove crazy outlier malaria
germsnumeric <- subset(germsnumeric, germsnumeric$X != "Malaria (P. falciparum)")

#yaxis transformations
germsnumeric$case.fatality.rate <- ifelse(germsnumeric$case.fatality.rate < 0.1, germsnumeric$case.fatality.rate * 100, ifelse(germsnumeric$case.fatality.rate < 1, germsnumeric$case.fatality.rate * (10) + 10, germsnumeric$case.fatality.rate + 20))

The plot (sorry)

#yaxis labels (Hannah's brilliant idea)
yax <- c(0, 0.1, 1, seq(10, 100, 10))
xax <- c(seq(-1,17,1))

#plot: deadlieness on x axis, contagiousness on y axis, color by transmission, continuous x scale 0-17, continuous y scale 0-100 with breaks at 0, 0.1, and 10. Hannah had a beautiful theme as well...
ggplot(germsnumeric, aes(x=average.basic.reproductive.rate, y=case.fatality.rate, colour=primary.mode.of.transmission)) + geom_point(size=5) + geom_text(aes(label=X), size=5, hjust=0, vjust=1) + scale_y_continuous(breaks= seq(0,120,by=10), minor_breaks = NULL, label=function(x){return(paste(yax, "%"))}) + scale_x_continuous(breaks= seq(-1,17,by=1), minor_breaks = NULL) + labs(title = "MicrobeScope Recreation!") + ylab("DEADLINESS (Percent of infected people who died)") + xlab("CONTAGIOUSNESS (Average Basic Reproductive Rate)") + scale_colour_discrete(name="Primary Mode of Transmission") + theme(plot.title = element_text(size=20, face="bold", hjust=0.5, vjust=1), axis.title.x = element_text(color="gray"), axis.title.y = element_text(color="gray"), legend.title = element_text(colour="gray"), legend.key = element_rect(fill=NA), legend.position = "top", panel.background = element_rect(fill = NA), panel.grid.major = element_line(linetype = "dotted", colour = "gray"), panel.border = element_rect(linetype = "dotted", colour = "gray", fill=NA))
